Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - This article investigates the governance role of banks exercised through the replacement of underperforming CEOs in borrowing firms. An average level of bank loans outstanding implies a 22% to 47% increase in the forced turnover probability of a borrowing firm?s CEO if a firm?s industry adjusted performance is one standard deviation below average. This increase is much larger, 68% to 92%, when an underperforming firm violates its loan covenants. Overall, the paper?s findings suggest that banks play a key role in the governance of underperforming firms, especially when covenants are violated.
ER  - 

